# Project-specific: raw market data and large binaries.
# Raw exchange snapshots (Binance Vision zips, kline/funding parquet) are
# fetched on demand and verified by SHA256 against a committed manifest, so the
# bytes themselves stay out of git; the manifest + derived/aggregated artifacts
# are what a reviewer regenerates from. data/raw is ignored; data/snapshots
# keeps only its manifest marker.
data/raw/
data/cache/
data/snapshots/*
!data/snapshots/manifest.toml
!data/.gitkeep
runs/
*.parquet
*.feather
*.h5
*.hdf5
*.duckdb
*.sqlite
*.zip
*.csv
!docs/**/*.csv
!tests/**/*.csv
# committed test fixtures: a tiny real Binance Vision funding zip + its checksum
!tests/data/*.zip

# Derived study artifacts: the committed, regenerable JSON artifact that the
# figures render from IS tracked (it carries no raw vendor data); large raw
# artifact dumps under artifacts/raw are not.
artifacts/raw/

# Secrets (defense in depth; .env covered above)
secrets/
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
credentials.json
service-account*.json

